Priestly class: Sikhism does not have a designated priestly class. In Sikhism, all individuals have equal access to connect with the divine and serve their community. This absence of a priestly class reflects the core belief in equality and emphasizes the importance of personal connection with God without the need for intermediaries. Sikhism promotes direct communication with the divine through meditation, selfless service, and living a moral life, highlighting the idea that spirituality is a personal journey that each individual is encouraged to undertake independently.
