Male Sikhs generally have Singh as their last name, which is a common practice among followers of the Sikh faith. Singh, meaning "lion" in Punjabi, is a revered name symbolizing courage, strength, and equality among Sikh men. It serves as a unifying factor among male Sikhs, emphasizing their commitment to their faith and community.
